column1: #Text=DS : Sune , you went through a period where you got really tired of LA and New York and traveled around the United States .
#Text=What did you find when you traveled across the country ?
#Text=It struck me how different the country was as I went south and north , and towards the middle .
#Text=It just struck me how really , really different it was .
#Text=Even when I was driving up to Canada once to get my visa , I rented a car from here and I was barely an hour outside of New York City everything changes so dramatically .
#Text=The way people were , the way people looked at you in a " Who are you , stranger ?

column1: #Text=I had the best time in the south ; people were so hospitable to me .
#Text=Everywhere I went they were like , ‘ Oh , you come from Denmark ?
#Text=That 's great ... I 'll give you this for free ! '
#Text=And when I go north , people treat me like I 'm crazy .

#Text=So I guess the answer to your question is that I was very surprised at how different it was from place to place , and then I started understanding when the election came up and people were voting Democratic here , Republican there , it all made sense to me all of a sudden .
#Text=I was like , " Oh , I see , those are people who never leave their state , never leave their town ...
